util

Class DistObjManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • util.DistObjManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Exporter, Importer

    public final class DistObjManager
extends java.lang.Object
implements Importer, Exporter
    Each process needs to manage its available distributed objects, as well as leases on remote objects. This class is in charge of this. Imports and Exports RemoteObjects via a RemoteObjFactoryImpl.

    Right now it assumes a Address + Known Addresses.

    See Also:
    RemoteObjFactoryImpl

    • Constructor Detail

      • DistObjManager

        public DistObjManager(java.util.List<io.atomix.catalyst.transport.Address> known,
                      io.atomix.catalyst.transport.Address me,
                      io.atomix.catalyst.transport.Transport t)
        Not using clique at all for dynamic networking.

        Simple parameterized constructor receives the Addresses that are known to the DistObjManager current process and the actual Address of the process it's in.

        We assume each process -> one server and/or client.

        Parameters:
        known - List of known addresses.
        me - The process's own address.
        t - The transport with which to work on setting up connections.

      • DistObjManager

        public DistObjManager(io.atomix.catalyst.transport.Address me,
                      io.atomix.catalyst.transport.Transport t)
        Not using clique at all for dynamic networking.

        Receives the actual Address of the process it's in.

        Assumes known addresses consist only of the default naming service.

        Parameters:
        me - The process's own address.
        t - The transport with which to work on setting up connections.

      • importCopy

        public java.util.Optional<java.lang.Object> importCopy(RemoteObj b)
                                                throws java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException,
                                                       java.lang.IllegalAccessException,
                                                       java.lang.NoSuchMethodException
        Returns a clone of a skeleton pointed to by a RemoteObj.

        Has to be done via reflection. (or manual monomorphization).

        Excepts out the wazoo.

        Parameters:
        b - the reference to be looked-up.
        Returns:
        A clone of a skeleton or empty.
        Throws:
        java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException - Due to calling clone via reflection.
        java.lang.IllegalAccessException - Due to clone being possibly not public.
        java.lang.NoSuchMethodException - If clone does not exist as a method.
        See Also:
        RemoteObj

      • sendRegisterRequest

        public void sendRegisterRequest(RegisterRequest rq)
        #TODO Should start a lease on the remote object store. Send a register request to the first known address, which defaults to the pre-established naming service (canonically localhost:10000).

        This request will be tried 3 times in a synchronized fashion and may except after failure with an unchecked exception.

        Does not require a special handler to be registered. Will use Connection.sendAndReceive(Object)

        Parameters:
        rq - The request to send.
